# Application Overview
eIdentificator is designed for searching and verifying students entering the university premises, as well as generating reports on identified students. It is integrated with a database containing information on all active students.
# Identification
The identification process is based on keyword search functionality. User can search by entering a value for the student’s index number, first name, or last name. If the keyword entered is incomplete, the application will display all students matching the provided parameters. The search is case-insensitive and ignores any extra spaces entered. The index number is searched individually, while first and last names can be searched in combination, regardless of order. If the keyword contains excess or incorrect characters, the student will not be found and a message indicating a non-existent student will be displayed.
Additional filters are available for year of study, type of study, and study program (department). The possible values for these filters are automatically updated based on the selection of other filters. These filters serve an analytical purpose but can also assist in identifying students, especially in cases where the database may contain partially incorrect data.
After the student list is displayed, you can check the "Identified" column for each student, which records the exact time of identification in the database. The displayed student data can be sorted by index number, first name, last name, or identification time by clicking the corresponding column header in the student table.
The total number of students identified for the current day is displayed and updates dynamically as students are verified.
At the start of each new day, the identification data is reset: all students become unidentified and previous identification times are cleared.
# Report
The Report tab provides statistics on identified students, including the total number of identified students, the number of identified students by type of study, and the percentage of identified students relative to the total number of active students.
A preview of the current student report (index number, first name, and last name) is available and can be sorted by first or last name in ascending or descending order. By clicking the "Generate Report" button, you can select the file name and type (the default is *.CSV, as it can be easily imported into spreadsheet applications) and save the report.
The "Reset Report" button allows you to delete all report data and reset the identification records for students.
